{"parse":{"title":"Flag Salute","pageid":46540853,"revid":818163961,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the poem. For the salute, see <a href=\"/wiki/Flag_salute\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flag salute\">Flag salute</a>.</div>\n<p>\"<b>Flag Salute</b>\" is a poem written by <a href=\"/wiki/Esther_Popel\" title=\"Esther Popel\">Esther Popel</a> about the <a href=\"/wiki/Lynching\" title=\"Lynching\">lynching</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/George_Armwood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"George Armwood\">George Armwood</a> on October 18, 1933 in <a href=\"/wiki/Princess_Anne,_Maryland\" title=\"Princess Anne, Maryland\">Princess Anne, Maryland</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cover_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cover-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-rice_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rice-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>   It was first published in August 1934 in <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Crisis\" title=\"The Crisis\">The Crisis</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Harlem_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Harlem-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and later republished in its entirety on the cover of <i>The Crisis</i> in 1940.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cover_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cover-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It juxtaposes the murder of Armwood with quotations from the <a href=\"/wiki/Pledge_of_Allegiance\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pledge of Allegiance\">Pledge of Allegiance</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bracks_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bracks-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\nThe poem reflects that <a href=\"/wiki/Lynching\" title=\"Lynching\">lynching</a> in the United States had become a \"ritual of interracial social control.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Selim_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Selim-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Flag_Salute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-cover-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-cover_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-cover_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archives.dickinson.edu/node/10310/zoomify\">\"<i>Flag Salute</i>\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Crisis\" title=\"The Crisis\">The Crisis</a></i>. <a href=\"/wiki/National_Association_for_the_Advancement_of_Colored_People\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Association for the Advancement of Colored People\">National Association for the Advancement of Colored People</a>: Cover. November 1940<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 April</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Crisis&amp;rft.atitle=Flag+Salute&amp;rft.pages=Cover&amp;rft.date=1940-11&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchives.dickinson.edu%2Fnode%2F10310%2Fzoomify&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFlag+Salute\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-rice-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-rice_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Rice, Anne P. (October 9, 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=xfSdgkSjsHUC&amp;lpg=PA282&amp;dq=esther%20popel%20flag%20salute&amp;pg=PA282#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Witnessing Lynching: American Writers Respond</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Rutgers_University_Press\" title=\"Rutgers University Press\">Rutgers University Press</a>. p.&#160;282. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0813533308\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0813533308\">978-0813533308</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 April</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Witnessing+Lynching%3A+American+Writers+Respond&amp;rft.pages=282&amp;rft.pub=Rutgers+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2008-10-09&amp;rft.isbn=978-0813533308&amp;rft.aulast=Rice&amp;rft.aufirst=Anne+P.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DxfSdgkSjsHUC%26lpg%3DPA282%26dq%3Desther%2520popel%2520flag%2520salute%26pg%3DPA282%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFlag+Salute\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Harlem-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Harlem_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">West, Sandra L. (September 1, 2003). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=XP48QWTmjyUC&amp;lpg=PA266&amp;dq=esther%20popel%20flag%20salute&amp;pg=PA266#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Encyclopedia of the Harlem Renaissance</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Amazon_Digital_Services\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Amazon Digital Services\">Amazon Digital Services, Inc.</a> p.&#160;266<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 April</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+the+Harlem+Renaissa